Add 300ml cold salted @water{300%ml} to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @sugar snap peas{150%g} widthways.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper.

Stir-fry until just starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @turkey mince{250%g} to the pepper and stir-fry until cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the turkey as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the turkey is browned, add the garlic and sugar snaps to the pan.

Stir-fry together for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{2%sachets} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if necessary.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between #bowls{}.

Top with the teriyaki turkey stir-fry.